This CL removes usage of the AbortSignalHandleBasedRemoval kill switch, which was added in M109.
Web NFC, Idle Detection, and Eyedropper were storing the AbortSignal to work around not having AbortSignal::RemoveAlgorithm(), needing to compare the "current signal" to the one causing the abort. This CL removes the checking and signal, where possible.
