Bug: 1313616 Change-Id: Iaf25a5d575e3d9f2fe1ef4af4c95a8ff0f4a5f6d Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/4415686 Reviewed-by: Allen Bauer <kylixrd@chromium.org> Code-Coverage: Findit <findit-for-me@appspot.gserviceaccount.com> Commit-Queue: Siyu An <siyua@chromium.org> Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#1130669}

The sanity checking of intermediates is currently inconsistently applied, with some ways of creating an X509Certificate enforcing it and others not.
In most cases this sanity checking of the intermediates by X509Certificate is pointless (when anything actually uses the intermediates they'll need to do much more parsing/checking than that anyway). It only really exists since CreateCertificateListFromBytes and CreateCertBuffersFromBytes can try to parse certificates from different file formats and use the sanity check to determine if the file format was correct or not. Make those methods call an internal function that does the sanity checking, and remove the use of the sanity checking from all other cases.
